#################################################################
#    Annotations
#################################################################

<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#CapabilityTradeCouncil> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An organization that replaces configuration steering boards, integrating operational and acquisition authorities into a single body that adjudicates requirement-versus-cost trades for a capability portfolio." ;
                                                                 rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform> ;
                                                                 rdfs:label "Capability Trade Council" ;
                                                                 <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An organization that replaces configuration steering boards, integrating operational and acquisition authorities into a single body that adjudicates requirement-versus-cost trades for a capability portfolio." ;
                                                                 <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier> "POLICY" .


<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#JointAccelerationReserve> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A funding source that is the CAPE-maintained (Cost Assessment and Program Evaluation) reserve established to address the valley of death between prototype demonstration and program of record funding." ;
                                                                   rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform> ;
                                                                   rdfs:label "Joint Acceleration Reserve" ;
                                                                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A funding source that is the CAPE-maintained (Cost Assessment and Program Evaluation) reserve established to address the valley of death between prototype demonstration and program of record funding." ;
                                                                   <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier> "POLICY" .


<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#JointForceRequirementsProcess> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A planned process that is the Joint Force Requirements Process (JFRP) that replaced JCIDS; under it the re-oriented Joint Requirements Oversight Council (JROC) ranks Key Operational Problems rather than validating prescriptive capability documents." ;
                                                                        rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform> ;
                                                                        rdfs:label "Joint Force Requirements Process" ;
                                                                        <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A planned process that is the Joint Force Requirements Process (JFRP) that replaced JCIDS; under it the re-oriented Joint Requirements Oversight Council (JROC) ranks Key Operational Problems rather than validating prescriptive capability documents." ;
                                                                        <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier> "POLICY" .


<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#KeyOperationalProblem> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An objective that is a prioritized joint-force operational problem ranked by the re-oriented Joint Requirements Oversight Council (JROC); the requirements root that replaced JCIDS capability documents." ;
                                                                rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform> ;
                                                                rdfs:label "Key Operational Problem" ;
                                                                <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An objective that is a prioritized joint-force operational problem ranked by the re-oriented Joint Requirements Oversight Council (JROC); the requirements root that replaced JCIDS capability documents." ;
                                                                <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier> "POLICY" .


<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#PortfolioAcquisitionExecutive> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An organization that is the single accountable portfolio office under the Defense Acquisition System reform, holding acquisition authority across a capability portfolio in place of a program-by-program Program Executive Office." ;
                                                                        rdfs:comment "This class represents the organizational office, not the role borne by a person." ;
                                                                        rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform> ;
                                                                        rdfs:label "Portfolio Acquisition Executive" ;
                                                                        <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An organization that is the single accountable portfolio office under the Defense Acquisition System reform, holding acquisition authority across a capability portfolio in place of a program-by-program Program Executive Office." ;
                                                                        <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier> "POLICY" .


<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#PortfolioScorecard> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A document content entity that is the Defense Acquisition System reform's data-driven portfolio performance record, whose primary measure is time-to-field." ;
